ite(btoa('REPLACEWITHHEXSTRVARIABLE'.match(/[\\da-f]{2}/gi).map((a)=&gt;String.fromCharCode(parseInt(a,16))).join('')))&lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Replace the <code>REPLACEWITHHEXSTRVARIABLE</code> fragment with the variable contaning the hexadecimal string, add a \"Get File of Type\" with type <code>com.apple.webarchive</code> below, and its output will be the base64 string. Show it with a \"Quick Look\" action to see it (a \"Show Results\" is not adequate because of the text centering and hyphenation).</p>\n<p>I use \"Get File of Type\" instead of \"Get Contents of Webpage\" to avoid that the user is misleading told that the shortcut uses Safari.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0 - Oct. 25, 2020, 4:19 p.m.</strong></p>"}